regular-way trades. Include both of the following: (a) all transactions in exchange-traded financial instruments that are expected to settle within the standard settlement cycle of that exchange (for example, two days for U.S. securities exchanges);
Under SEC Release No. 34-96930, Shortening the Securities Transaction Settlement Cycle, the SEC amended Rule 15c6-1, Settlement Cycle Rule, to shorten the standard settlement cycle for most broker-dealer transactions from two business days after the trade date (T+2) to one business day after the trade date (T+1).
and (b) all transactions in cash-market-traded financial instruments that are expected to settle within the time frame prevalent or traditional for each specific instrument (for example, for U.S. government securities, one or two days).
